Package runnables

Class SampleAnalyserRunnable

java.lang.Object
runnables.SampleAnalyserRunnable
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
public final class SampleAnalyserRunnable
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable
Implementation of the Runnable interface to analyze a sample.

Runs a sample analysis in a single thread.

Since:
2.0
Version:
2.0
Author:
Simon Hackl

      public SampleAnalyserRunnable​(java.lang.String sampleName, ReferenceFeatureEntry referenceFeatureEntry, htsjdk.samtools.util.CloseableIterator<htsjdk.variant.variantcontext.VariantContext> variantInformation, VariantContentTable variantContentTable, double minCoverage, double minHomFrequency, double minHetFrequency, double maxHetFrequency, double minQuality, me.tongfei.progressbar.ProgressBar progress)
      Constructor of SampleAnalyserRunnable.
      Parameters:
      sampleName - String the samples name.
      referenceFeatureEntry - ReferenceFeatureEntry information about the reference to which respect the sample is analyzed.
      variantInformation - htsjdk.samtools.util.CloseableIterator<htsjdk.variant.variantcontext.VariantContext> returned by a VCFFileReader giving access to the single input `.vcf` files entries.
      variantContentTable - VariantContentTable to store the processed information.
      minCoverage - Double minimum coverage specified by the user.
      minHomFrequency - Double minimum hom. call frequency (wrt. read support) specified by the user.
      minHetFrequency - Double minimum het. call frequency (wrt. read support) specified by the user.
      maxHetFrequency - Double maximum het. call frequency (wrt. read support) specified by the user.
      minQuality - Double minimum quality specified by the user.
      progress - ProgressBar to indicate runtime information.

    • processVariantCall

      private void processVariantCall​(int variantPosition, double variantQuality, double variantCoverage, double variantFrequency, htsjdk.variant.variantcontext.Allele variantAllele, htsjdk.variant.variantcontext.Allele referenceAllele, boolean isHetCall, boolean isMFA, java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> additionalAnnotation)
      Internal method to process a variant-call.
      Parameters:
      variantPosition - String the position of the variant.
      variantQuality - Double the quality of the variant.
      variantCoverage - Double the coverage of the variant.
      variantFrequency - Double the frequency of the variant.
      variantAllele - Allele the alternative allele information.
      referenceAllele - Allele the reference allele information.
      isHetCall - Boolean to indicate if the variant originates from a het. call; necessary to apply the correct filter method.
      isMFA - Boolean to indicate if the variant originates from the most frequent allele.
      additionalAnnotation - String an additional annotation string that is added to the entry.
